billion, not $1 trillion.)  The  International Monetary Fund  is
proposing to raise its lending capacity by $500 billion to
insulate the global economy against any worsening of  Europe â€™s
debt crisis, according to a person familiar with the
discussions.  The Washington-based lender currently has $385 billion
